@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title Partitioning Spreads Load Across Servers

left to right direction

actor "Client Group A" as clientA
actor "Client Group B" as clientB
actor "Client Group C" as clientC

node "Router /\nPartition Map" as router #E6F3FF

clientA --> router : requests for partition A
clientB --> router : requests for partition B
clientC --> router : requests for partition C

node "Server A\nSmaller queue" as serverA #E6FFE6
node "Server B\nSmaller queue" as serverB #E6FFE6
node "Server C\nSmaller queue" as serverC #E6FFE6

router --> serverA
router --> serverB
router --> serverC

note bottom of router #FEFFDD
  Instead of one hot queue on one machine,
  load is divided across multiple servers.
end note

note bottom of serverB #E6F3FF
  Partitioning increases aggregate throughput
  and pushes the saturation knee to the right.
end note

@enduml
